description:
One of the only five Iberian endemic monotypic genera. This observation is from the type locality of the species. The population has just been rediscovered more than 40 years after the species description. 
https://www.diariodesevilla.es/vivirensevilla/redescubren-sevilla-planta-dada-extinguida_0_2003890712.html

taxon.name: Gyrocaryum oppositifolium

taxon.wikipedia_summary: Gyrocaryum is a genus of plant in family Boraginaceae. It contains a single species, Gyrocaryum oppositifolium, which is endemic to Spain.
